java having 8 primitive datatypes
byte  --1 byte --0
short --2 byte --0
int   --4 byte --0
long  --8 byte --0
char  --2 byte --'\u000'
float --4 byte --0.0f
double--8 byte --0.0d

boolean--not defined -- false

String --not defined --null

-----Wrapper classes---------

1.Wrapper classes is nothing but converting the primitive datatypes to object
2. Primitive datatypes does not belong to any class, so collections will support only Objects instead of primitive data types. 
3. All the wrapper classes present under  Object class (Boolean, Number and Charecter are the wrapper classes).
4. All the number related classes are the subclasses of Abstract class called Number.


